        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 4:34PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 434 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southwest of Lake Marvin, or 8 miles southeast of Canadian,
moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Canadian, Glazier, and Lake Marvin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
